The paper deals with the optimization of power amplifiers (PAs) in a massive MIMO system, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The load adaptive nature of the system and the consideration of daily traffic profiles suggest that it may also fall under the categories of control systems (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the use of queueing theory to model the base stations suggests that it may also fall under the category of architecture (cs.AR).
